The quest for the Presidency has been in the centre of a cycle of unending animosity, dividing Kenya along ethnic lines. A few months after the handshake even before the building bridges task force gets down to work a leadership split called ‘hustlers versus dynasties” is threatening to destabilize Kenya yet again as 2022 talks gain momentum. But the recent meeting between President Uhuru Kenyatta, his DP William Ruto and NASA leader Raila Odinga might be seen as a move to end the narrative of divisive politics ahead of the 2022 poll but will that help cure the notion that was emerging about a political fight between the dynasties, the hustlers, the bureaucrats and everyone else. 